#Text=Chapter 22
#Text=Anne went home to think over all that she had heard .
#Text=In one point , her feelings were relieved by this knowledge of Mr Elliot .
#Text=There was no longer anything of tenderness due to him .

#Text=He stood as opposed to Captain Wentworth , in all his own unwelcome obtrusiveness ; and the evil of his attentions last night , the irremediable mischief he might have done , was considered with sensations unqualified , unperplexed .
#Text=Pity for him was all over .
#Text=But this was the only point of relief .
#Text=In every other respect , in looking around her , or penetrating forward , she saw more to distrust and to apprehend .

#Text=She was concerned for the disappointment and pain Lady Russell would be feeling ; for the mortifications which must be hanging over her father and sister , and had all the distress of foreseeing many evils , without knowing how to avert any one of them .
#Text=She was most thankful for her own knowledge of him .
#Text=She had never considered herself as entitled to reward for not slighting an old friend like Mrs Smith , but here was a reward indeed springing from it !
#Text=Mrs Smith had been able to tell her what no one else could have done .
#Text=Could the knowledge have been extended through her family ?
#Text=But this was a vain idea .

#Text=She must talk to Lady Russell , tell her , consult with her , and having done her best , wait the event with as much composure as possible ; and after all , her greatest want of composure would be in that quarter of the mind which could not be opened to Lady Russell ; in that flow of anxieties and fears which must be all to herself .

#Text=She found , on reaching home , that she had , as she intended , escaped seeing Mr Elliot ; that he had called and paid them a long morning visit ; but hardly had she congratulated herself , and felt safe , when she heard that he was coming again in the evening .
#Text=" I had not the smallest intention of asking him , " said Elizabeth , with affected carelessness , " but he gave so many hints ; so Mrs Clay says , at least . "
#Text=" Indeed , I do say it .
